}}\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} align=\"right\" |58,192\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |55.7%\n|\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Gabriela Saucedo Mercer\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} align=\"right\" |46,185\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |44.3%\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[U.S. House election, 2016|2016]]\n|\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |{{nowrap|'''Ra\u00fal M. Grijalva*'''}}\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} align=\"right\" |148,973\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |100%\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\nGrijalva and his wife Ramona have three daughters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grijalva.house.gov/index.cfm?sectionid=87&sectiontree=2,87|title=Congressman Raul Grijalva: Biography|publisher=House.gov|accessdate=November 9, 2010}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of Hispanic and Latino Americans in the United States Congress]]\n{{Portal bar|Biography}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [http://www.tucsoncitizen.com/video/player.php?file=032206grijalva1 Videos of Grijalva discussing various issues] ''Tucson Citizen'', March 22, 2006\n* [http://grijalva.house.gov/uploads/Grijalva_Public_Lands_Report_10_22_20081.pdf A Report on the Bush Administration Assaults On Our National Parks, Forests and Public Lands], October 22, 2008\n* [http://www.democracynow.org/2009/10/30/grijalva Rep. Raul Grijalva, Vows to Bring Public Option to House Floor] - video report by ''[[Democracy Now!]]'', October 30, 2009\n* [http://www.democracynow.org/2010/5/28/arizona Rep. Raul Grijalva: New Deployment of National Guard to US-Mexico Border Is Election-Year \"Political Symbolism\"], May 28, 2010\n\n==External links==\n* [http://grijalva.house.gov/ Congressman Raul Grijalva] official U.S. House site\n* [http://www.standwithraul.com/ Grijalva for Congress]\n* {{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/Arizona/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/Raul_Grijalva_%5BD-3%5D}}\n* {{CongLinks | congbio=g00055